ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How much do you agree with the following statements about using the internet for health-related information: You know how to find helpful health information on the internet?
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Somewhat disagree; 2 = Neither agree nor disagree; 3 = Somewhat agree; 4 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: How much do you agree with the following statements about using the internet for health-related information: You can tell high quality from low quality health information on the internet?
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Somewhat disagree; 2 = Neither agree nor disagree; 3 = Somewhat agree; 4 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: How much do you agree with the following statements about using the internet for health-related information: You feel confident in using information from the internet to make health decisions?
Notes: 0 = Strongly disagree; 1 = Somewhat disagree; 2 = Neither agree nor disagree; 3 = Somewhat agree; 4 = Strongly agree

ElementDescription: Have you ever used a digital tool to help with your mental health (i.e., interventions delivered via apps, mobile and web-based platforms)?
Notes: 0 = No; 1 = Yes

ElementDescription: What are the most important things you would want from a digital mental health intervention: Stress management strategies?
Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

ElementDescription: What are the most important things you would want from a digital mental health intervention: Communication or assertiveness training?
Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

ElementDescription: What are the most important things you would want from a digital mental health intervention: Help managing emotions (e.g., depression, anxiety, anger)?
Notes: 0 = Not at all important; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very important

ElementDescription: If you selected 'something else' for the most important thing you would want from a digital mental health intervention, please briefly describe.
How helpful would you find each of these teaching approaches in a digital mental health intervention: Reading materials as the main way of providing information?
Notes: 0 = Not at all helpful; 1 = Not very; 2 = Somewhat; 3 = Very helpful
